    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-10-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-10-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="97"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d97">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">341.115 St 2/37½</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Wilson</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-10-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 22, 1914</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Lansing</hi>: I quite agree with you that the
                    only course to take in the matter of the tank steamer <hi rend="italic"
                        >Brindilla</hi> and in other similar cases is to make an immediate and
                    vigorous protest against the action of the British authorities in seizing an
                    American vessel bound to a neutral port.</p>
                <p>In haste</p>
                <p>Cordially and faithfully yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Woodrow Wilson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
